### MCP Systems Controller - Admin & Simulation API
# HITL Demonstration flow.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@operatorId = radesh-govind

### 1. Simulate an Agent Request
# This triggers a destructive 'docker_stop_container' tool call.
# The system will intercept this and return a PENDING status with an Action ID.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/approvals/simulate-agent
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. List Pending Approvals
# Run this to see the "Plan of Action" (PoA) currently waiting in the Gate.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/approvals
Accept: application/json

### 3. Resolve (Approve) an Action
# Replace {actionId} with the ID returned from Step 1 or Step 2.
# Setting 'approved=true' will trigger the actual Docker/K8s command.
@actionId = 190a7cad-a4bc-48f4-8736-b50859c92b5d
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/approvals/{{actionId}}/resolve?approved=true&operatorId={{operatorId}}

### 4. Resolve (Reject) an Action
# If you reject, the action is discarded and never reaches the infrastructure.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/approvals/{{actionId}}/resolve?approved=false&operatorId={{operatorId}}

### 5. Check Prometheus Metrics
# See the real-time counters for approved vs. rejected actions.
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/prometheus
